author: Ash-kyun
text:
Normally I'm not one for ASMR videos as they just feel all sorts of.... weird I guess, to be frank. Having isolated audio in one ear is a little disorienting. However, since this is Rushia, I had to make an exception. Rushia's voice normally is just so soothing, pleasant and just makes me smile and melt my heart, so having that voice felt like being whispered directly into your ears is all new kind of serene, sublime euphoria. It's as if Rushia's voice is designed for ASMR. I really hope we get some more in the future.

Isn't it ironic though; she's supposed to be a necromancer, but with streams like this, she's much more attuned to be a cleric/healer. Her voice just has that power that make a bad day non-exisistent and just heals you in mind, body and soul. Thank you Rushia for always being a radiant personality you are a precious individual. Bless your BOING BOING heart. We all love you, please never stop. :_ハート::_おこなのです:

author: Amai Ta. Yume
text: This is the first time I'm going to write in a vtuber content. This might be long, but please bear with me. I've been watching a lot and like the HoloLive Franchise a lot. I've been watching many as I do now. If someone ask me who is my favorite, I wouldn't have said anything, because I like them all equally. But the ring fitness where Rushia got extremely tired, I couldn't help but sympathize her feeling after the stream. I worried and worried a lot about it. It was my first time to check the Rushia's twitter figuring it out if she's okay. All of a sudden, I saw her tweet that she's doing a surprise livestream! I was happy she was okay, yet worried because of her health. But I was astonished, excited to watch her thing and I don't know this tingly feeling happening inside. When I see my comment appearing at her steam, no matter if it appears or not, I was so proud, because I get to be in the community with her. Again, I never knew this feeling still now. I still never knew that yesterday, she hadn't stream for the whole day or night. And while I was watching others, Rushia keeps appearing in my head over and over again. "Why can't I stop thinking about this necromancer." All day long, I can't stop thinking about Rushia or when she'll appear  I got lonely. That was then when I saw this ASMR in the hololive schedule, I feel euphoric, Extremely happy, enjoyed, and my heart can't stop beating. I don't know what kind of feeling is this. This is new for me. I'm glad I get to see Rushia, connect with her at some point, even if I don't know any nihonggo yet. I can read, but cannot understand them yet. At that point during the ASMR, the mic was clunky, but I fixed my settings, and every time I can feel her breath, heart and voice, I can always feel that she's beside me. With that, I'm not alone, and I'm happy that I'm not alone. This was one of her charms. Her love to her fans was so much. I want to be considered as a fan, but I couldn't give super chat or stickers yet, or become a membership. One day, perhaps, I keep thinking to myself. I still don't know this feeling, but I feel like I don't want to stop seeing Rushia or being with her. I don't know this feeling to much but I feel really comfortable. This is also my first free time and my first time that I get to watch Rushia from beginning at the end. I also have this feeling that I hope Rushia would reply to this comment. But even if she were not to reply, I just seeing her and thinking about her future livestreams, I don't think I'll give up.
